## 4. Bug Tracking

JJ's Bugs:
Bug 1.) reviewSuggestions.php threw a fatal PDO error on load. The MemberSuggestion table did not exist in the database because Kah's submission form was inserting into MemberSuggestion while the SQL file only contained a Suggestion table.
Resolution: Created the MemberSuggestion table in phpMyAdmin with the correct columns matching Kah's insert statement: suggestion_id, user_id, suggestion_text, attachment_path, status, and created_at.
Severity: High | Fix Status: Fixed

Bug 2.) reviewSuggestions.php threw a fatal PDO error after adding the resolved-by feature. The resolved_by column did not exist in the MemberSuggestion table.
Resolution: Added the resolved_by column to the MemberSuggestion table via phpMyAdmin using ALTER TABLE MemberSuggestion ADD COLUMN resolved_by INT NULL with a foreign key referencing User(user_id).
Severity: High | Fix Status: Fixed

Bug 3.) Review Suggestions link returned a 404 Not Found error when clicked from the homepage.
Resolution: index.php is located inside the loginpages folder while reviewSuggestions.php is in the root. Updated the link in index.php to use ../reviewSuggestions.php to correctly navigate up one directory level.
Severity: High | Fix Status: Fixed


Shannon's Bugs:
Bug 1.) change tracking in lanja_db.sql 
        The audit log updated successfully with the update triggers, but I noticed all the json attributes updated for that row, 
        even the ones that had no changes. It’s hard to see what changes were made to the json object arrays without playing spot the difference. 
Resolution: Created a procedure that filters out the difference between the before and after json. Added diff_json attribute to AuditLog table. 
Severity: low | Fix Status: Fixed

Bug 2.) fixed session variable in userInfo.php 
        I get ‘user_id cannot be null’ error when choosing updated_by attribute for user table update trigger, specifically when activating/deactivating users. 
        I haven’t received this error for the other triggers I tested. Replacing updated_by with user_id stops this error but doesn’t receive the proper value in the database. The error shows it’s on line 41 from userInfo.php.
Resolution: I added updated_by to the deactivate query. Then, I got fk constraint error but have no fks in User, which is the table that is being updated. I used var_dump() for all the ID variables (current user & user being updated) 
        to find out the current_user_id is showing as an array. I just forgot to put [‘user_id’] next to $_SESSION[‘user’]. 
Severity: low | Fix Status: Fixed

Bug 3.) trouble displaying correct role_name in viewLog.php
        When i made a join query for the user role, it returned all roles of the current user, but I only want to see the role that the user was logged into al the time of making the changes. 
Resolution: I added a $current_role_id variable that is seen and used by the database trigger. I also added role_id to AuditLog table to perform a join query for the user’s role. 
Severity: high | Fix Status: Fixed

Bug 4.) CSV won’t launch in viewLog.php 
        When I click export csv button, I get ‘undefined variable’ error for variables positioned above the action button statement where the csv execute block is held. Var_dump() shows 
        these variables hold correct values before the export csv button is clicked. I know it has something to do with the form sending to the same page, causing it to refresh and the variables clear. 
Resolution: I tested this by placing the export query in a different page called exportLogs.php, which launches when Admin user clicks export all button. 
        I also made changes to the csv query block section, separating the json keys from values, so that the file output looks more organized. 
Severity: med | Fix Status: Fixed

